1
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:19,030
He knew he didn't have long to live.

2
00:00:19,830 --> 00:00:21,030
That's why he asked you

3
00:00:21,030 --> 00:00:22,440
to lock Pans inside

4
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:25,160
so he could die together
with the monster,

5
00:00:26,440 --> 00:00:26,920
right?

6
00:00:31,620 --> 00:00:35,620
=Cases Between Us=

7
00:00:35,980 --> 00:00:38,900
=Episode 23=

8
00:02:13,030 --> 00:02:14,430
He saved that puppy,

9
00:02:15,430 --> 00:02:17,400
hoping you'd both go on living.

10
00:02:22,310 --> 00:02:23,520
For his sake as well.

11
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:52,190
Cry it out.

12
00:02:53,470 --> 00:02:54,680
No one's going to laugh at you.

13
00:03:14,980 --> 00:03:18,300
(Chengnan Children's Home)

14
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:23,910
Please take good care of her.

15
00:03:24,310 --> 00:03:25,030
Don't worry.

16
00:03:26,190 --> 00:03:27,710
We'll visit you often.

17
00:03:34,224 --> 00:03:36,000
She's asking
if you've got your job back.

18
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:37,750
I have.

19
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:38,310
Thank you.

20
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,430
Let's go.

21
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:50,630
I have a friend in Jinan.

22
00:03:50,770 --> 00:03:52,310
He met Pans five years ago.

23
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,840
Back then, there was a little girl

24
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:54,870
about this tall with him.

25
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:57,150
That beast

26
00:03:57,824 --> 00:04:00,000
stole their chance
to grow up like normal children.

27
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,400
How old are you?

28
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:09,520
Eighteen?

29
00:04:30,976 --> 00:04:32,360
What are you two talking about?

30
00:04:35,430 --> 00:04:36,750
She says she'll miss us.

31
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,680
A thank-you gift from Director Li.

32
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:11,950
He's been transferred to Customs.

33
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,480
He made it?

34
00:05:15,390 --> 00:05:17,040
He studied economics.

35
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:19,232
The Police Department
was not the right place for him.

36
00:05:20,144 --> 00:05:22,272
As for the methamphetamine
we're investigating,

37
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:23,360
since he's at Customs now,

38
00:05:23,456 --> 00:05:25,248
might as well have him help us
look into it.

39
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,830
The Japanese are slippery.

40
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:28,128
They're not easy to investigate.

41
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,040
Chief,

42
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:46,630
the Commissioner

43
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:47,950
wants you back on duty immediately.

44
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:50,240
The Division Four needs you.

45
00:05:50,304 --> 00:05:52,384
- We can't do without you.
- We can't do without you.

46
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,160
Chief Yuan,

47
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,680
they're giving you

48
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:58,270
quite the welcome.

49
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:07,950
Here you go.

50
00:06:13,222 --> 00:06:16,222
(Jingshi Police Department)

51
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:21,480
The British Embassy

52
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:23,800
wants Father Pans extradited.

53
00:06:24,510 --> 00:06:25,120
Sorry?

54
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:26,560
No way.

55
00:06:26,752 --> 00:06:28,070
He tortured and abused children.

56
00:06:28,070 --> 00:06:30,750
The evidence is conclusive.
He must stand trial here!

57
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:32,480
Enough.

58
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:34,560
I'm telling you,

59
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,950
this is an order from above.

60
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:37,950
Above who?

61
00:06:37,950 --> 00:06:39,008
I'll talk to them myself.

62
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:40,480
Talk to them?

63
00:06:40,830 --> 00:06:42,070
There you go again.

64
00:06:42,830 --> 00:06:44,040
You just...

65
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:47,600
You just got reinstated.

66
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:48,870
I'm begging you.

67
00:06:48,870 --> 00:06:51,008
Could you please keep your head down
for a few days?

68
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,360
I'm not asking for much.

69
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,160
Just give me two days.

70
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,160
I'll think of something.

71
00:06:59,270 --> 00:06:59,750
I...

72
00:07:00,630 --> 00:07:03,190
Having you as my subordinate

73
00:07:03,510 --> 00:07:05,510
takes years off my life.

74
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,680
Three days.

75
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,750
Three days tops.

76
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:15,920
Yes, sir.

77
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,472
Don't worry. I've written the article.

78
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,250
It goes to print
first thing tomorrow morning.

79
00:07:21,260 --> 00:07:23,530
I've contacted the newspapers
with the largest circulation.

80
00:07:23,540 --> 00:07:25,300
We'll expose everything
the priest has done.

81
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,720
The evidence is conclusive.

82
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,040
He deserves the death penalty.

83
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:31,270
I'm just worried
someone higher up will interfere.

84
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:38,040
That's why we need to make this
as public as possible.

85
00:07:38,128 --> 00:07:40,016
Politicians care most
about their reputations.

86
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:41,360
Only then

87
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,160
will they think twice.

88
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:45,680
What if they resort to
dirty tricks again?

89
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:47,360
Yuan Hong will be fine.

90
00:07:47,424 --> 00:07:48,830
But I might get involved again.

91
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:50,600
Give me a gun.

92
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,750
What do you need a gun for?

93
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:53,792
Keeping your nose clean
would help more than anything.

94
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:58,160
You're going back to school tomorrow.

95
00:07:58,160 --> 00:07:59,310
Otherwise, I'll tell Father

96
00:07:59,310 --> 00:08:00,560
to cancel your enrollment.

97
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:03,190
I'm not going.

98
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:04,000
Zhao Shaoshang!

99
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,040
Think about Father for once.

100
00:08:12,310 --> 00:08:13,510
He's the Minister of Education.

101
00:08:13,750 --> 00:08:14,870
If you keep skipping school,

102
00:08:14,912 --> 00:08:16,960
how's he supposed to oversee
the universities?

103
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:21,310
Shaoshang.

104
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:35,120
Why does he
hate going to school so much?

105
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,840
Well,

106
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,320
you can't blame him.

107
00:08:43,150 --> 00:08:43,860
What?

108
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,150
You don't want

109
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:46,390
to do my homework?

110
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:49,010
Why are you so stubborn?

111
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:51,220
Use your brain.

112
00:08:52,140 --> 00:08:53,700
Listen, I'm giving you the honor

113
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:54,740
of doing my homework.

114
00:08:57,536 --> 00:08:59,392
And you're dragging your feet.

115
00:08:59,504 --> 00:09:01,540
You poor little brat.
Stop pretending to be a snob!

116
00:09:02,380 --> 00:09:03,020
Hand it over.

117
00:09:04,380 --> 00:09:05,220
Give it to me!

118
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:14,420
Zhao Shaoshang?

119
00:09:18,060 --> 00:09:19,260
This has nothing to do with you.

120
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:23,568
Now that I've seen it,
it has something to do with me.

121
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,860
You have three seconds. Get lost.

122
00:09:27,020 --> 00:09:28,660
Or I'll make sure everyone in Beijing

123
00:09:28,660 --> 00:09:29,940
knows your father's corruption.

124
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:34,220
One.

125
00:09:36,940 --> 00:09:37,620
Two.

126
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:38,620
Go.

127
00:09:38,860 --> 00:09:39,340
Quick.

128
00:09:55,952 --> 00:09:57,792
You never fight back
when people hit you.

129
00:09:58,112 --> 00:09:59,936
Does your book matter more
than your life?

130
00:10:04,580 --> 00:10:05,620
Thanks.

131
00:10:06,780 --> 00:10:07,860
You're like a toothpick.

132
00:10:12,260 --> 00:10:13,940
If anyone bullies you again,
come find me.

133
00:10:14,224 --> 00:10:16,592
There's nothing at Yenching University
I can't handle.

134
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:20,340
New here?

135
00:10:21,260 --> 00:10:21,940
What's your name?

136
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:24,100
Chen Mingyuan.

137
00:10:24,768 --> 00:10:26,800
Ming, as in impartial
and incorruptible justice,

138
00:10:26,832 --> 00:10:27,900
(Chen Mingyuan)

139
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:29,880
and Yuan, as in inner peace
leads to great vision.

140
00:10:32,540 --> 00:10:33,260
Good name.

141
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,968
I picked it up
from Liulichang Antique Market.

142
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:48,900
Take a look.

143
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:54,820
Zhao,

144
00:10:55,490 --> 00:10:58,580
you don't have to help me
look for books anymore.

145
00:11:01,940 --> 00:11:03,340
Don't like my taste?

146
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:04,500
You haven't even looked.

147
00:11:05,232 --> 00:11:07,180
The church scholarship
checks my associations.

148
00:11:07,568 --> 00:11:09,840
Getting too close to the children
of powerful families

149
00:11:10,768 --> 00:11:12,672
means I no longer qualify
as a needy student.

150
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:19,660
Children of powerful families?

151
00:11:28,060 --> 00:11:28,540
Fine.

152
00:11:30,380 --> 00:11:31,620
We'll keep our distance.

153
00:11:49,740 --> 00:11:51,100
It's Zhao Shaoshang again.

154
00:11:51,296 --> 00:11:52,820
Young Master Zhao's in trouble again.

155
00:11:53,220 --> 00:11:54,100
What's it this time?

156
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:55,740
He stole the exam papers.

157
00:11:56,860 --> 00:11:58,420
He's completely out of control.

158
00:11:59,380 --> 00:12:00,180
Tell me about it.

159
00:12:00,540 --> 00:12:01,540
It's always him.

160
00:12:01,820 --> 00:12:02,300
Exactly.

161
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:04,220
(Report)
He has an influential father.

162
00:12:04,220 --> 00:12:05,220
(Zhao Shaoshang Stole the Final Exam Papers)
Anyone else

163
00:12:05,328 --> 00:12:07,024
would've been expelled already.

164
00:12:10,580 --> 00:12:11,420
Young Master Zhao,

165
00:12:11,620 --> 00:12:13,020
losing your temper?

166
00:12:14,180 --> 00:12:16,340
Don't tell me it's true.

167
00:12:16,820 --> 00:12:18,380
His father is the Minister of Education.

168
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:20,940
Getting hold of an exam paper
would be as easy as saying the word.

169
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:23,712
So what if my father
is the Minister of Education?

170
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:25,200
Since he's the Minister of Education,

171
00:12:25,248 --> 00:12:26,100
if I wanted to cheat,

172
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:27,648
why would I need someone
to take the exam for me?

173
00:12:27,664 --> 00:12:28,940
I'd just have all of you fail.

174
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,640
Now you're throwing your weight around.

175
00:12:30,660 --> 00:12:31,500
Look at Chen Mingyuan.

176
00:12:31,510 --> 00:12:32,900
You bullied him badly
that he doesn't dare come to class.

177
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:34,420
Does Minister Zhao know

178
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:36,500
his son is acting like a tyrant
at school?

179
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,140
Exactly.

180
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:39,420
Go ahead and tell him.

181
00:12:39,536 --> 00:12:41,380
We'll see whether he sides with me
or with you.

182
00:12:44,580 --> 00:12:45,780
What a piece of work.

183
00:12:46,128 --> 00:12:47,540
Just because his father's powerful.

184
00:12:47,860 --> 00:12:49,340
Poor Chen Mingyuan.

185
00:12:56,460 --> 00:12:57,220
Why?

186
00:13:01,420 --> 00:13:02,580
Because of that scholarship?

187
00:13:10,180 --> 00:13:10,780
Zhao,

188
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:12,940
you were born rich.

189
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:14,900
You'll never know

190
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:16,780
how much that money means to me.

191
00:13:17,584 --> 00:13:18,540
If I stay close to you,

192
00:13:19,424 --> 00:13:21,140
I'll only feel more ashamed of myself.

193
00:13:21,952 --> 00:13:22,784
Just think of me

194
00:13:26,660 --> 00:13:27,900
as a petty man.

195
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:01,380
Later, when the forged transcript
was exposed,

196
00:14:01,380 --> 00:14:02,660
he transferred to Nanyang.

197
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,512
But everyone in the schools said

198
00:14:04,528 --> 00:14:07,060
Shaoshang had used his family's
influence to drive him away.

199
00:14:08,860 --> 00:14:10,460
Didn't anyone speak up for him?

200
00:14:11,740 --> 00:14:12,940
My brother

201
00:14:13,820 --> 00:14:14,860
has the softest heart

202
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:16,500
and the sharpest mouth.

203
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:19,020
The less he explained,

204
00:14:19,740 --> 00:14:21,420
the wilder the rumors became.

205
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:23,830
Repeat a lie often enough,
and people will believe it.

206
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:26,660
In the end, even the professors
and the chancellor looked down on him.

207
00:14:27,568 --> 00:14:28,944
They never stopped to think

208
00:14:28,944 --> 00:14:30,650
that if he really
threw his weight around,

209
00:14:30,660 --> 00:14:32,060
would he be living like this?

210
00:15:03,260 --> 00:15:04,820
Young Master Zhao,

211
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:06,540
what a rare guest.

212
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:08,700
Once in a blue moon.

213
00:15:10,060 --> 00:15:11,060
What's so funny?

214
00:15:11,060 --> 00:15:12,180
Stop laughing.

215
00:15:12,180 --> 00:15:14,340
You'll make Young Master Zhao angry.

216
00:15:14,688 --> 00:15:15,820
What if he has his father

217
00:15:15,820 --> 00:15:17,220
get you all expelled?

218
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:18,380
Exactly.

219
00:15:18,540 --> 00:15:19,540
Don't provoke him.

220
00:15:19,540 --> 00:15:21,632
He might even have the professor's
pay and bonuses

221
00:15:21,664 --> 00:15:22,300
docked.

222
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:23,540
As if he could.

223
00:15:23,950 --> 00:15:25,420
Why couldn't he?

224
00:15:25,770 --> 00:15:26,890
In all of Jingshi,

225
00:15:26,980 --> 00:15:28,060
besides murder and arson,

226
00:15:28,340 --> 00:15:30,370
is there anything Young Master Zhao
wouldn't dare do?

227
00:15:30,660 --> 00:15:31,740
He skips class all the time,

228
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:32,980
and nothing happens.

229
00:15:33,740 --> 00:15:35,100
Anyone else

230
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:36,900
would've been expelled years ago.

231
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:39,180
Who'd dare cross him?

232
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:41,620
Are you here to attend class

233
00:15:41,620 --> 00:15:43,300
or daydream?

234
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:45,300
If you want to enjoy
the sunshine, go outside.

235
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:47,060
There's not much sunshine
in this classroom.

236
00:16:03,740 --> 00:16:04,780
Who are you?

237
00:16:06,380 --> 00:16:08,580
We're from Division Four
of the Jingshi Police Department.

238
00:16:08,610 --> 00:16:10,170
By order of the Commissioner,

239
00:16:10,330 --> 00:16:12,860
we're here to present Mr. Zhao Shaoshang
with a commendation.

240
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:16,180
A commendation?

241
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:18,220
What for?

242
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:26,820
Previously,

243
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:29,984
Mr. Zhao Shaoshang assisted
the Police Department

244
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:32,260
with criminal investigations
in his spare time.

245
00:16:32,780 --> 00:16:34,700
In just a few months, he helped crack

246
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:36,380
the Blood Fluke Case,

247
00:16:36,380 --> 00:16:37,340
the Eight Alleys Case,

248
00:16:37,340 --> 00:16:38,380
the Eight-Armed Nezha Case,

249
00:16:38,380 --> 00:16:39,540
the Longevity Pill Case,

250
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:40,860
and the Priest Child Abuse Case.

251
00:16:41,020 --> 00:16:42,420
He set a new Police Department record

252
00:16:42,580 --> 00:16:44,100
for solving cases.

253
00:16:45,232 --> 00:16:46,100
Really? Zhao Shaoshang?

254
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:47,820
He put his own life on the line

255
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:48,980
and braved danger several times

256
00:16:48,980 --> 00:16:51,420
to help bring the real culprit
to justice.

257
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:52,460
Here,

258
00:16:52,900 --> 00:16:55,260
on behalf of everyone
at the Police Department,

259
00:16:55,260 --> 00:16:56,928
I'd like to express
our heartfelt gratitude

260
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:58,060
to Mr. Zhao Shaoshang.

261
00:16:58,380 --> 00:16:58,940
Now,

262
00:16:59,340 --> 00:17:01,660
please welcome him to the stage
to receive his commendation.

263
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:07,220
Shaoshang,

264
00:17:07,740 --> 00:17:08,780
come up.

265
00:17:09,460 --> 00:17:10,140
Shaoshang,

266
00:17:10,540 --> 00:17:11,380
come.

267
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:12,460
Come on.

268
00:17:16,540 --> 00:17:17,860
He's my student.

269
00:17:19,380 --> 00:17:19,860
Come.

270
00:17:23,820 --> 00:17:24,340
Come.

271
00:17:30,060 --> 00:17:32,220
I heard that while helping solve cases,

272
00:17:32,220 --> 00:17:33,700
you never neglected your studies,

273
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:34,900
ranking first in every subject.

274
00:17:35,420 --> 00:17:37,660
Mr. Zhao, please take care of yourself.

275
00:17:37,660 --> 00:17:38,580
Cherish your life.

276
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:39,780
You were lucky to survive

277
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:42,100
that last shootout.

278
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:43,300
There was a shootout?

279
00:17:43,460 --> 00:17:44,580
- Shootout?
- What?

280
00:17:45,180 --> 00:17:46,220
- Seriously?
- My gosh.

281
00:17:48,380 --> 00:17:48,980
That's right.

282
00:17:49,376 --> 00:17:50,740
Mr. Zhao was ambushed in his car

283
00:17:50,740 --> 00:17:52,260
